name: Shohei Ohtani
summary: Shohei Ohtani continues to make history, swiftly following up his 40-40 milestone with another home run. In an extraordinary 9th inning, he hit a grand slam, becoming the fastest player in MLB history to join the 40-40 club. Ohtani's remarkable achievement has sparked speculation about whether he could become the first player to reach 50-50. His exceptional performance has even led some to believe he aspires to become the greatest player in baseball history. Currently, Ohtani is approaching his first 40-40 season with the Los Angeles Dodgers, showcasing his exceptional abilities as both a pitcher and hitter.
